The input `positions` is a 2D integer array.
The length of `positions` is between 1 and 1000.
Each element in `positions` is an array of length 2.
The first element of each array in `positions` represents the left coordinate of the square.
The second element of each array in `positions` represents the side length of the square.
The left coordinate of each square is between 1 and 10^8.
The side length of each square is between 1 and 10^6.
